      <Content>According to ancient Jewish tradition, the end of the age would be characterized by a heavenly feast to be enjoyed by the righteous. This would be presided over by Abraham, and therefore to go to Abraham’s bosom would be equivalent to being an honored guest at this celestial banquet.</Content>
